<div class="answercell post-layout--right">
        <div class="js-endorsements" data-for-answer="24469279">
</div>

    
    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>As an alternative, you could do something like this, using your 'Solution 1':</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-class"><span class="hljs-keyword">class</span> <span class="hljs-title">ChoreDoer</span>
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-keyword">private</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$mover</span>;

    <span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">__construct</span>(<span class="hljs-params">Tourist <span class="hljs-variable">$t</span></span>)
    </span>{
        <span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;tourist = <span class="hljs-variable">$t</span>;
    }

    <span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">checkEmails</span>(<span class="hljs-params"/>)
    </span>{
        <span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">getMover</span>()-&gt;<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">gotoInternetCafe</span>();
    }

    <span class="hljs-keyword">public</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">meetGirlfriend</span>(<span class="hljs-params"/>)
    </span>{
        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span> (<span class="hljs-title class_">Girlfriend</span>::<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">location</span>() === <span class="hljs-string">'restaurant'</span>)
        {
            <span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">getMover</span>()-&gt;<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">gotoRestaurant</span>();
        }<span class="hljs-keyword">else</span>
        {
            <span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">checkEmails</span>();

        }
    }
    <span class="hljs-comment">/**
     * lazy-load mover object
     */</span>
    <span class="hljs-keyword">private</span> <span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">getMover</span>(<span class="hljs-params"/>)
    </span>{
        <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(<span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;mover == <span class="hljs-literal">null</span>)
        {
            <span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;mover = <span class="hljs-keyword">new</span> <span class="hljs-title class_">Mover</span>(<span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;tourist);
        }
        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;mover;
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>If you don't fancy using the  getter, you could instead name your property something like</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-keyword">private</span> <span class="hljs-variable">$_mover</span>;
</code></pre>

<p>And use a magic __get to call your getter for you:</p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-function"><span class="hljs-keyword">function</span> <span class="hljs-title">__get</span>(<span class="hljs-params"><span class="hljs-variable">$property</span></span>)
</span>{
    <span class="hljs-variable">$method</span> = <span class="hljs-string">'get'</span>.<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">ucfirst</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$property</span>);
    <span class="hljs-keyword">if</span>(<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">method_exists</span>(<span class="hljs-variable">$method</span>))
    {
        <span class="hljs-keyword">return</span> <span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;<span class="hljs-variable">$method</span>();
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>Although this will not perform quite as well, it makes it easy to just call </p>

<pre class="lang-php s-code-block"><code data-highlighted="yes" class="hljs language-php"><span class="hljs-variable language_">$this</span>-&gt;mover-&gt;<span class="hljs-title function_ invoke__">gotoInternetCafe</span>();
</code></pre>

<p>And is nice and clean.</p>
